com.alvo.runner.checking

Class Either<L,R>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.alvo.runner.checking.Either<L,R>
  • Type Parameters:
    L - Type parameter of first(LEFT) value.
    R - Type parameter of second(RIGHT) value

    public abstract class Either<L,R>
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a value of one of two possible types (a disjoint union.) An instance of Either is either an instance of left or right. e.g.: Can contain the value of type L OR R in the same time.

      • map

        public abstract <T> T map(java.util.function.Function<? super L,? extends T> leftF,
                          java.util.function.Function<? super R,? extends T> rightF)
        Basic projection(mapping) over the Either monad. Accepts 2 functions for LEFT and RIGHT values and maps the corresponding function over the presented(single existing) value (LEFT or RIGHT)
        Type Parameters:
        T - desired projection type.
        Parameters:
        leftF - function for mapping over the LEFT value. Accepts supertype for LEFT value type and returns value of type T.
        rightF - function for mapping over the RIGHT value Accepts supertype for RIGHT value type and returns value of type T.
        Returns:
        value of projected type T.
